snippet.textDisplay:
I wish all the news networks would stop using misleading graphs for the sake of sensationalism. The majority of American's can comprehend the direness of the situation, compounding it with sensationalism doesn't help the situation. I'm sure the numbers are accurate but let's say one state has 10 confirmed case one day and then 90 the next day, that can also be portrayed as 800% increase. More information should be shown and made available so everyone can better understand the statistics. It's usually never enough to just show an "in the nutshell" result because most, if not all of the time, it will be taken the wrong way.

Finally, the numbers aren't going up solely because more and more new people are getting infected. The numbers are up because more test are being done on those infected in the past and present. The numbers are also going up because Asymptomatic people infected weeks ago are finding out they have it. SARS-COVID-19 has been with us since day 1.
